Diagram 3 (Correct)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White's attachment at 1 is the blind spot in which the vital point hides. This most likely leaves black stunned. There is no countermeasure.
\par
\par From 2 to 5, black's death is demonstrated. You cannot find a move like white 1 easily unless you are very attentive.
\par }
