Diagram 4 (A Practice Problem)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par This is a similar position but the technique is the same.
\par
\par \b White to Play.\b0
\par After white 1 is exchanged for black 2, the problem is the same. However, even without the 1-2 exchange, white can attach at 3 and kill black.
\par
\par Please check for yourself.
\par }
